def: Past; -- applied to a tense which expresses an action or stateas past.
To ordain or appoint beforehand; to preordain; to predestinate;to predetermine. Hooker.
To chafe; to enrage; to heat. [Obs.] Shak.
Of or pertaining to a manor. " Manorial claims." Paley.

An instrument, consisting usually of a wireloop or noose, forremoving tumors, etc., by avulsion. Snare drum, the smaller commonmilitary drum, as distinguished from the bass drum; -- so calledbecause (in order to render it more resonant) it has stretched acrossits lower head a catgut string or strings.
A South American rodent (Myopotamus coypus), allied to thebeaver. It produces a valuable fur called nutria. [Written alsocoypou.]
